Last Broadcast Date: Thu 13 Oct 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Abdulnasser Gharem, the Saudi Army officer who has become the country's leading contemporary artists. Also, the American protesters who've taken their anger against the Wall Street banks to Washington DC, and are now camping out in Freedom Plaza. And the British financial trader who has spent more than $90,000 for a ticket to travel into space. Show less